🔍 Installation Steps (Local + AWS): 📥 Install kind:

curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.22.0/kind-linux-amd64
chmod +x ./kind
sudo mv ./kind /usr/local/bin/kind


📦 Install kubectl (Ubuntu):
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl
sudo curl -fsSLo /usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes-archive-keyring.gpg https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes-archive-keyring.gpg] \
https://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y kubectl


✅ Check versions:

kind --version
kubectl version --client


🏗️ Create Your First Cluster!

kind create cluster --name=new-cluster
docker ps              # See containers
kubectl get nodes      # See cluster nodes


✅ Delete cluster:

kind delete cluster --name=new-cluster


⚙️ Create Multi-node Cluster with kind:
✏️ Create config:

# config.yml
kind: cluster
apiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4
nodes:
- role: control-plane
  image: kindest/node:v1.31.2
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.31.2
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.31.2

kind create cluster --name=my-cluster --config=config.yml
kubectl get nodes


🐳 Let’s Deploy a Pod!

kubectl run nginx --image=nginx
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod nginx
kubectl delete pod nginx


🧹 Clean Up:

kind delete cluster --name=my-cluster



